{
  "stem": "12491.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Krakow ghetto was actually a stopover airport for many wounded Germans who came from the east coast-- from the east-- [INAUDIBLE] it's not east coast-- I'm sorry-- the east front.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But these Germans, the officers, German officers, who were assigned to the Krakow-- they didn't care about them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They only cared about what can they do for themselves.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was while we still were living in ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One day a train arrived on the siding inside the airport, and several people were taken away from their work, from their job, to unload the train.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The train consisted of equipment-- primarily uniforms, boots, socks, belts-- what-- shirts, et cetera-- for many thousands of-- of soldiers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were designated to carry that to different warehouses.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They had several warehouses.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Shirts went here, boots were somewhere else, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The following morning, we were brought by truck from ghetto, and we went, as usual, back to work.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "After a few minutes at work, a soldier came up and he says, Joseph, you are to report to the [GERMAN] commandant-- whatever-- the man who's in charge of the uniforms and equipment.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I did-- I come there, and there were several people already sitting.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Some of them were Jews and some of them were Polish, because Polish people also worked at the airport, coming in every morning from the outside to work.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there was a long table set up, and behind the table there were German officers with a marker [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It's something similar to American MP, military police.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the commandant of the group which we were-- we were responsible to was sitting at a desk at a distant corner.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was just the-- more like an overseer, but not involved in the interrogation which was to take place.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
